mid stage dementia and their loved ones/carers to deal with feelings of uncertainty and insecurity after the diagnosis- and to prepare for and manage changes and challenges positively. Through a mindful and positive psychology approach- the kit will support and empower persons with dementia- and thus reduce strain on carers. It willincrease empathy and mutual understanding to strengthen the relationship between both.</p><h4>How long has your idea existed?</h4><p>4 months - 1 year</p><h4>This idea emerged from</h4><p>A group brainstorm</p>,5,"It’s a very viable program because it’s something that people want, it’s being done through a partnership that can get grants in funds in order to get the program done.",I think that when you are trying to help people that are dealing with dementia it’s always going to be a desirable thing because this is something that is tough to understand and a lot of people deal with it.,Since the program is partnering with a University it makes it much more feasible because they always have grants and stuff that they can use for programs like these.,5,5,5,5,5
